com.github.mrgoro.interactivedata.api.data.operations

Class Operation<D extends OperationData,O extends OperationData>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.mrgoro.interactivedata.api.data.operations.Operation<D,O>
  • Type Parameters:
    D - Type of the Request Data Object
    O - Type of the Options Object
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Filter, Function, Granularity

    public abstract class Operation<D extends OperationData,O extends OperationData>
extends java.lang.Object
    Generic definition of an operation. An Operation does "something" with a field in a data set. As an operation is abstract it cannot directly be instantiated.

    Operation is the base type of Filter, Granularity and Function.

    Operations are parameterized with request data and options. Options are set once. Request data originates from a specific request and is therefore set per request. Operation.Builder helps creating these instances with changing request data. The Framework automatically populates the data for options and requests. Filters only have to specify the form of the data with custom OperationData classes.

    Author:
    Philipp Schürmann
